\\"\\n        Update the status of a task.\\n        :param task_id: Unique identifier for the task\\n        :param status: New status of the task (e.g., \'In Progress\', \'Completed\')\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        if task_id in self.tasks:\\n            self.tasks[task_id][\'status\'] = status\\n        else:\\n            raise ValueError(f\'Task with ID {task_id} not found.\')\\n\\n    def track_performance(self, team_member, metric, value):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Track performance metrics for a team member.\\n        :param team_member: Name of the team member\\n        :param metric: Performance metric (e.g., \'tasks_completed\', \'efficiency\')\\n        :param value: Value of the performance metric\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        if team_member not in self.performance:\\n            self.performance[team_member] = {}\\n        self.performance[team_member][metric] = value\\n\\n    def get_task_details(self, task_id):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Get details of a specific task.\\n        :param task_id: Unique identifier for the task\\n        :return: Dictionary containing task details\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        return self.tasks.get(task_id, None)\\n\\n    def get_performance(self, team_member):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Get performance metrics for a specific team member.\\n        :param team_member: Name of the team member\\n        :return: Dictionary containing performance metrics\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        return self.performance.get(team_member, None)"\n}\n```\n\nThis code defines a `TeamCollaborationManager` class with methods to create tasks, update task statuses, track performance metrics, and retrieve task and performance details. This aligns with the requirements for the `Team_Collaboration_Manager` application.', role='assistant', tool_calls=None, function_call=None, provider_specific_fields=None)
