tric = max(0, min(1, efficiency_metric))  # Clamp between 0 and 1\\n\\n    return efficiency_metric"}]}}'}], 'summary': 'Based on the provided results from the agents, it appears that the initial implementation of the `CollaborativeBuildOptimizer` class was reviewed and revised by each agent. However, the class name and its purpose do not align with the task requirements for `Team_Collaboration_Manager`. The task requires a program that facilitates collaboration among team members with tools for task management, communication, and performance tracking, rather than a build optimizer.\n\nHere is a revised version of `solution.py` that aligns with the task requirements:\n\n```python\n# solution.py\n\nclass TeamCollaborationManager:\n    """\n    The Team Collaboration Manager class is designed to facilitate collaboration among team members\n    by providing tools for task management, communication, and performance tracking.\n    This class provides methods to create and assign tasks, set deadlines, track progress,\n    and evaluate performance.\n    """\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        """\n        Initialize the TeamCollaborationManager with empty data structures for tasks and performance tracking.\n        """\n        self.tasks = {}  # Dictionary to store tasks with their details (e.g., assignee, deadline, status)\n        self.performance = {}  # Dictionary to store performance data for team members\n\n    def create_task(self, task_id, description, assignee, deadline):\n        """\n        Create a new task and assign it to a team member.\n        """\n        self.tasks[task_id] = {\n            \'description\': description,\n            \'assignee\': assignee,\n            \'deadline\': deadline,\n            \'status\': \'Pending\'\n        }\n\n    def update_task_status(self, task_id, status):\n        """\n        Update the status of a task.\n        """\n        if task_id in self.tasks:\n            self.tasks[task_id][\'status\'] = status\n\n    def track_progress(self):\n        """\n        Track the progress of all tasks.\n        """\n        return self.tasks\n\n    def evaluate_performance(self, member_id, performance_data):\n        """\n        Evaluate and store performance data for a team member.\n        """\n        if member_id not in self.performance:\n            self.performance[member_id] = []\n        self.performance[member_id].append(performance_data)\n\n    def get_performance(self, member_id):\n        """\n        Retrieve performance data for a team member.\n        """\n        return self.performance.get(member_id, [])\n```\n\nThis revised `solution.py` includes a `TeamCollaborationManager` class with methods to create and manage tasks, track progress, and evaluate performance, which aligns with the task requirements. The final deliverable in JSON format is as follows:\n\n```json\n{\n  "solution.py": "# solution.py\\n\\nclass TeamCollaborationManager:\\n    \\"\\"\\"\\n    The Team Collaboration Manager class is designed to facilitate collaboration among team members\\n    by providing tools for task management, communication, and performance tracking.\\n    This class provides methods to create and assign tasks, set deadlines, track progress,\\n    and evaluate performance.\\n    \\"\\"\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Initialize the TeamCollaborationManager with empty data structures for tasks and performance tracking.\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        self.tasks = {}  # Dictionary to store tasks with their details (e.g., assignee, deadline, status)\\n        self.performance = {}  # Dictionary to store performance data for team members\\n\\n    def create_task(self, task_id, description, assignee, deadline):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Create a new task and assign it to a team member.\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        self.tasks[task_id] = {\\n            \'description\': description,\\n            \'assignee\': assignee,\\n            \'deadline\': deadline,